5:
Such good weather we're having.
Why, it's perfect for...
13:
Only accompanied by fine tea and
even finer companions, of course.
17:
Aren't you supposed to be doing
some inspecting? Or did you come
to the orphanage just to have tea?
20:
I can assure you that I'm conducting
a thorough inspection.
28:
It's good to see you all! The letters
you send are always wonderful, but
it's even better to greet you in
person.
29:
We're joined today by my friend, Alk.
Are you ready to show us how your
minds have matured?
31:
Then let's start with a quiz. First
question!
33:
You have been asked to complete
an urgent errand, but you come
across a child who has been
separated from his mother. What do
you do?
36:
I'd take him to a guard, and then
finish the errand!
39:
An excellent response that
addresses both problems. You'd be
well suited for a job that aids others.
42:
Next question. You receive a
delicious treat for a job well done,
but on your way home, you meet
someone who is starving. What do
you do?
45: Mister Miguel, can that person work?
48:
Maybe they can, maybe they can't.
What would you do in either
situation?
51:
I'd give it and ask the person who
can work to help me earn more food.
52:
If the person can't work... I'd look for
someone who can help them learn
how to work!
55:
That plan is not without its risks, but
there is merit in taking on a
challenge.
57:
You would make an excellent
merchant—one suited to running a
large business. I have high hopes for
you.
64:
This is the orphanage I sponsor. One
day, when the children grow up,
they shall be employed by the Guild.
67:
So that whole quiz thing was figuring
out what kinda jobs to give them?
70:
That, and to see how they've
progressed in their studies. It's quite
an entertaining experience for all
involved.
72:
Raising children is a long-term
investment that will only pay off if
done right. If you want proof, you
need not look further than me.
74:
I secured a future through my own
efforts, but I would not have had the
ability to do so without the ones who
nurtured me.
75:
It is the duty of those who come
before to pave the way for those
who follow after.
77:
And now it is my turn to do the
paving...
80:
I won't spare any effort to make their
future worthwhile—not here, and not
as a diplomat.
84:
I've never thought that far ahead
before, but I see your point.
87:
What kind of future have you
pictured for yourself, Alk?
90:
Me? Honestly, I'm so busy with the
present, I haven't really considered
anything past that.
92:
Really? Well, I suppose you are busy
with your wild adventures.
94: I have a proposal for you then.
101:
I shall invest in you—do whatever I
can to aid you until you can think of
a future you'd like to work toward.
104:
I hope you're not planning to collect
interest on that.
107:
The only compensation I ask is that
you do what you can to keep the
world running. Any monetary
rewards from jobs will still be yours.
110:
So what you're saying is, we'll go on
the same way we always have.
112:
The terms of service between us
have been updated. That is all.
115: Now that sounds shady as heck...
122: Anyway, where are we headed next?
126:
There is a workplace that employs
the youths who have left the
orphanage...
